# UI Template

Global placeholder. Project-specific config lives in the project's `.cursor/rules/30-ui-template.mdc`.

## Fallback (no project config)

```
designer: standard Material Design / HTML conventions, no template components
fe-dev:   vanilla HTML/CSS or framework-agnostic components
NEVER assume Bootstrap / Tailwind / Metronic
Flag output: "ui_template: none configured — using framework-agnostic patterns"
```

## Agent behavior with this config

| Agent      | Use                                                           |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `designer` | Reference component names when describing UI flows            |
| `fe-dev`   | Use template components directly, follow token system         |
| `ba`       | Match screen types (list/form/dashboard) to template patterns |

## Project-level config template

Create `.cursor/rules/30-ui-template.mdc` in project:

```markdown
---
description: UI template config for this project
alwaysApply: false
---

# UI Template: {Template Name}

ui_template:
name: {e.g. Metronic 9}
version: {e.g. 9.2.0}
framework: {React | Vue | Angular | HTML}
component_library: {e.g. Tailwind + Radix | Bootstrap 5}
icon_set: {e.g. Font Awesome 6 | Heroicons}
theme_tokens_path: {path to CSS variables or token file}

## Key Components

- {ComponentName}: {when to use}

## Anti-patterns (do NOT use)

- {e.g. custom modal — use KTModal instead}
```
